WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:05.586
[ Kaleo's "Broken Bones" plays ]

00:10.181 --> 00:11.802
♪ I been down ♪

00:11.802 --> 00:13.554
Meredith: The harder the hit,
the more it'll sting.

00:13.554 --> 00:16.137
That's usually the case.

00:16.137 --> 00:18.059
So we prescribe.

00:18.059 --> 00:22.813
Meds, ice,
compression, elevation.

00:22.813 --> 00:25.646
Things you do
to stop the immediate pain.

00:25.646 --> 00:27.948
You left early
this morning.

00:27.948 --> 00:30.111
Alex: Yeah, 'cause
I love it here so much.

00:30.111 --> 00:32.153
I had to open,
plus it looks good.

00:32.153 --> 00:33.824
-Is that what the lawyer said?
-Supposed to establish that

00:33.824 --> 00:35.786
I'm a valuable member
of the community.

00:35.786 --> 00:38.329
You know, to counteract the fact
that I ruined DeLuca's face.

00:38.329 --> 00:40.711
I meet with them today.
Strategy session.

00:40.711 --> 00:43.164
They say it's make or break,
whatever that means.

00:43.164 --> 00:45.336
But you can only
dull the pain for so long,

00:45.336 --> 00:46.797
and when the drugs
start to wear off...

00:46.797 --> 00:48.669
♪ I saw my chance,
so I got him at last ♪

00:48.669 --> 00:50.631
...it really hurts.

00:50.631 --> 00:52.052
Thank you
for offering to help.

00:52.052 --> 00:54.265
I love you,
and I feel for you.

00:54.265 --> 00:57.518
Solidarity and all of that,
but this is scut.

00:57.518 --> 00:59.140
♪ Oh, he'll never say a word
no more ♪

00:59.140 --> 01:01.061
Don't think for one second
you're getting points

01:01.061 --> 01:02.353
for arriving before me.

01:02.353 --> 01:04.185
Things you didn't do
yesterday --

01:04.185 --> 01:05.736
refill
the glove dispenser,

01:05.736 --> 01:07.358
check the auxiliary
thermometer batteries,

01:07.358 --> 01:08.989
stock oral swabs.

01:08.989 --> 01:10.741
I'm out.
And what, you think this is
a place to --

01:10.741 --> 01:11.902
to hang out
with your friends?

01:11.902 --> 01:14.155
[ Scoffs ]
You do realize we open in 20,

01:14.155 --> 01:16.457
so you gonna sit there
and admire me or do you
want to get to work?

01:16.457 --> 01:19.460
[ Sighs ]

01:21.622 --> 01:24.125
It's a big thing
for me not to know.

01:24.125 --> 01:25.966
What is?
Which one?

01:25.966 --> 01:28.339
The church one --
that you go to church.

01:28.339 --> 01:29.970
You go to AA.
That's a lot of praying.

01:31.592 --> 01:32.883
What are we gonna tell
the children

01:32.883 --> 01:34.975
about God
and the afterlife or --

01:34.975 --> 01:36.597
Wait, the children?

01:36.597 --> 01:37.848
What children?

01:37.848 --> 01:39.180
Our children.

01:39.180 --> 01:40.811
So we're having
children now?

01:40.811 --> 01:42.433
No!
How can we have children?

01:42.433 --> 01:43.434
I barely know you.

01:49.150 --> 01:50.941
You know,
I had a thought.

01:50.941 --> 01:55.115
You and I should, uh...

01:55.115 --> 01:56.947
hang out together.

01:56.947 --> 01:58.329
You know,
somewhere that isn't here.

01:58.329 --> 02:00.331
Like, uh...

02:00.331 --> 02:01.662
a movie?

02:01.662 --> 02:02.873
No.

02:02.873 --> 02:05.166
Maybe I could
just show up there,

02:05.166 --> 02:06.837
and then you show up,

02:06.837 --> 02:08.839
and hey, look,
we're hanging out.

02:08.839 --> 02:10.090
I don't hang out.

02:10.090 --> 02:12.593
You could.

02:12.593 --> 02:14.715
Come on.
We're in the clear.

02:14.715 --> 02:17.348
Pierce asked me out.
I let her down gently.

02:19.019 --> 02:20.100
We could try.

02:20.100 --> 02:21.722
There's no trying.

02:21.722 --> 02:23.474
We are not
that type of friends.

02:23.474 --> 02:25.025
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

02:25.025 --> 02:27.438
All right, well,
what type of friends are we?

02:28.439 --> 02:30.191
I'm leaving.

02:35.276 --> 02:37.488
It's progress.

02:37.488 --> 02:40.080
Sorry I'm late.
What do we have?

02:40.080 --> 02:41.992
Jackson, uh...

02:44.084 --> 02:46.587
[ Chuckles ]

02:50.130 --> 02:51.131
Dr. Avery!

02:51.131 --> 02:51.962
Yeah, I'll get her.

02:53.003 --> 02:54.215
Hey.
Hey.

02:54.215 --> 02:56.217
Just, um, catching up.

02:56.217 --> 02:57.258
Tough night with Harriet?

02:57.258 --> 02:58.849
[ Yawning ]
She got up like six times.

02:58.849 --> 03:00.100
Or maybe seven.

03:00.100 --> 03:01.432
Ooh.

03:01.432 --> 03:03.724
Does it count
if she wakes

03:03.724 --> 03:05.226
just as we're
putting her back down?

03:05.226 --> 03:07.358
"We"?
What, you and April?

03:07.358 --> 03:09.570
No, you guys -- You have to
switch off, take turns.

03:09.570 --> 03:10.691
Yeah, I know.
We are, totally.

03:10.691 --> 03:12.233
I mean, kind of.

03:12.233 --> 03:13.904
It's just, you know,
she's recovering from surgery,

03:13.904 --> 03:15.816
so every time it's her turn,

03:15.816 --> 03:17.778
I still get up
and see how she's doing,

03:17.778 --> 03:19.240
which makes her
feel guilty,

03:19.240 --> 03:21.532
so then she tries to come
and help when it's my turn,

03:21.532 --> 03:23.784
and I spend that entire time
trying to convince her

03:23.784 --> 03:26.957
that she needs to get rested up
for -- for her turn.

03:26.957 --> 03:28.459
Which you then
get up for, too.

03:28.459 --> 03:30.130
[ Yawning ]
It's not a perfect system.

03:30.130 --> 03:32.253
But, um, I'm ready to work,
you know?

03:32.253 --> 03:33.834
I'm just --
I'm cranking away right here.

03:33.834 --> 03:34.885
Yeah, um,
well, tell you what.

03:34.885 --> 03:36.547
I'll take point on rounds

03:36.547 --> 03:38.679
by way of the coffee cart,
and, um...

03:38.679 --> 03:40.261
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

03:40.261 --> 03:43.474
Or not.
Uh, got a trauma on the helipad.

03:43.474 --> 03:45.686
-You're on your own.
-Yeah, a couple minutes.

03:46.647 --> 03:47.978
[ Sighs ]

03:47.978 --> 03:50.190
-Hold that elevator.
-Yep.

03:50.190 --> 03:52.273
Hey.

03:52.273 --> 03:54.775
-You look tired.
-[ Chuckles ]

03:54.775 --> 03:57.778
Well, I've been up a while with
Amelia talking and talking.

03:57.778 --> 04:00.120
She's yours now.
I'm not taking her back.

04:00.120 --> 04:02.493
I'm good. She's great.
We're -- We're great.

04:02.493 --> 04:03.914
[ Elevator bell dings ]

04:03.914 --> 04:06.166
You have the rest of
this elevator ride. Go.

04:06.166 --> 04:07.628
[ Sighs ] You know,
she gets an idea into her head

04:07.628 --> 04:09.209
and she just
won't let it go.

04:09.209 --> 04:11.171
She's relentless, like a --
like a shark.

04:11.171 --> 04:13.083
She just won't put it down.
-Two more floors.

04:13.083 --> 04:14.465
And she asks me a question
and I answer it,

04:14.465 --> 04:16.216
and my answer just causes
more questions,

04:16.216 --> 04:19.049
and suddenly I-I-I've forgotten
what we're talking about

04:19.049 --> 04:20.180
and I'm late for work.

04:20.180 --> 04:22.142
And I love her,
and it's exhausting.

04:22.142 --> 04:24.845
-Do you feel better?
-Yeah, a little bit.

04:24.845 --> 04:27.518
Glider plane crashed
near Snoqualmie Falls.

04:27.518 --> 04:29.189
Two passengers,
both conscious at the scene.

04:29.189 --> 04:31.442
Is Polly behind me?
She's my wife.

04:31.442 --> 04:33.314
Is she okay?
I need to see her. Please.

04:33.314 --> 04:35.736
Polly Campbell, 33,
B.P.'s 90 over 40.

04:35.736 --> 04:37.448
Blunt trauma to the chest
and abdomen.

04:37.448 --> 04:38.609
Where's Daniel?
Is he okay?

04:38.609 --> 04:39.900
We've got him.

04:45.075 --> 04:47.748
Timir [sighs]
I wanted to ask a favor.

04:47.748 --> 04:49.670
Look, I need to leave for
about an hour this afternoon,

04:49.670 --> 04:51.171
but I can be back
before close.

04:51.171 --> 04:53.714
I know you consider this
grunt work, Dr. Karev.

04:53.714 --> 04:55.876
It's a far cry from the hallowed
halls of the surgical floor.

04:55.876 --> 04:57.338
I-I didn't say that.

04:57.338 --> 04:59.590
Oh, and I'm sure you're not used
to taking orders from a nurse.

04:59.590 --> 05:00.381
Oh, no, it's fine.
I just

05:00.381 --> 05:02.012
Oh, is it fine?

05:02.012 --> 05:03.303
Thank you.

05:03.303 --> 05:05.926
This is second Thursday.
Vaccination day.

05:05.926 --> 05:07.558
We're about to get flooded
by hundreds of patients

05:07.558 --> 05:08.929
needing shots
on top of everyone else.

05:08.929 --> 05:10.561
I wouldn't ask
if it wasn't important.

05:10.561 --> 05:12.643
What's important
is our patients.

05:12.643 --> 05:15.235
They can't be rescheduled
like elective surgeries.

05:15.235 --> 05:18.148
They need you here and so do I.
The answer's no.

05:18.148 --> 05:19.490
You figure out your life
on your own schedule.

05:19.490 --> 05:21.151
Clinic's open.

05:21.151 --> 05:22.403
Get the doors.

05:26.116 --> 05:28.499
Pierce, you see this page?
Cardio consult in the pit.

05:28.499 --> 05:30.451
Oh, well, if you're going --

05:30.451 --> 05:31.712
You want to go?
I don't have to go.

05:31.712 --> 05:33.333
No, you --
you're already going.

05:33.333 --> 05:34.915
Why would I go?
-'Cause you were going.

05:34.915 --> 05:36.377
Well, I'm not, though,
if you are.

05:36.377 --> 05:37.378
So I'll go.

05:37.378 --> 05:38.719
And I will not go.

05:38.719 --> 05:40.801
Excuse me.
-Okay.

05:40.801 --> 05:43.303
Okay.

05:43.303 --> 05:44.555
I want to see my husband.

05:44.555 --> 05:45.966
Try and hold still
for me.

05:45.966 --> 05:48.729
Is Daniel hurt? Can --
Can you at least tell me that?

05:48.729 --> 05:49.930
He's in the other room
getting checked out.

05:49.930 --> 05:51.231
There's some fluid
in the belly.

05:51.231 --> 05:52.893
We're gonna need a C.T.
to take a better look.

05:52.893 --> 05:54.354
Was your husband flying
the glider?

05:54.354 --> 05:56.066
It was his first time up there
without an instructor,

05:56.066 --> 05:57.978
and he wanted me to go.
[ Inhales sharply ]

05:57.978 --> 06:00.150
He worked so hard for his.
[ Inhales sharply ]

06:00.150 --> 06:02.403
-SATs are dropping.
-She's gonna need a chest tube.

06:02.403 --> 06:05.486
[ Voice breaking ] Please,
please tell me he'll be okay.

06:05.486 --> 06:06.747
I got him, Polly,

06:06.747 --> 06:08.869
but I need to make sure
you can breathe first, okay?

06:08.869 --> 06:10.200
-Okay, how can I help?
-Lido.

06:10.200 --> 06:11.792
28 French,
and set up a pleurovac.

06:11.792 --> 06:14.455
Still dropping.
SATs are down to 88.

06:14.455 --> 06:15.626
I've got it.
Will you move?

06:17.297 --> 06:19.129
Polly, I'm sorry.

06:19.129 --> 06:21.131
Aah!

06:21.131 --> 06:23.554
[ Groans ]

06:23.554 --> 06:25.426
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

06:25.426 --> 06:28.849
[ Breathing heavily ]

06:28.849 --> 06:30.681
[ Exhales deeply ]

06:32.142 --> 06:33.724
There you go.

06:40.441 --> 06:41.822
How is he?

06:41.822 --> 06:43.363
Superficial
facial lacerations.

06:43.363 --> 06:44.825
But right leg, though.

06:44.825 --> 06:47.698
I'm fine.
Please, go help my wife.

06:47.698 --> 06:49.029
Meredith:
She's asking for you, too.

06:49.029 --> 06:50.451
She's being treated
in the next room.

06:50.451 --> 06:52.412
I'm telling you I'm fine.

06:52.412 --> 06:55.456
♪♪

07:01.341 --> 07:03.504
I'm gonna need sandbags
and a spinal x-ray.

07:03.504 --> 07:04.505
Okay.

07:04.505 --> 07:06.046
I just want to see Polly.

07:06.046 --> 07:07.848
Daniel, I'm gonna need
to get a spinal x-ray.

07:07.848 --> 07:09.009
I can't feel my legs.

07:09.009 --> 07:10.851
Okay, I don't want you
to be alarmed.

07:10.851 --> 07:13.263
No, no, I mean I haven't
felt them for three years.

07:13.263 --> 07:15.145
I'm paraplegic.

07:15.145 --> 07:16.937
Oh. Well, okay.

07:16.937 --> 07:19.229
Polly: Where's Daniel?
I want to see him!

07:19.229 --> 07:20.771
Daniel!

07:20.771 --> 07:22.653
-Owen, stop.
-Sweetie, you there?

07:22.653 --> 07:23.614
Daniel?

07:23.614 --> 07:25.776
I-I-I'm here!
Are you okay?

07:25.776 --> 07:27.367
-Are you all right?
-Are you okay?

07:27.367 --> 07:28.829
-I'm all right.
-I'm okay, I think.

07:28.829 --> 07:31.702
Polly,
I-I wish I could see you.

07:31.702 --> 07:33.203
I love you so much.

07:33.203 --> 07:34.705
I love you, too.

07:34.705 --> 07:36.957
Polly, I'm so sorry!

07:37.417 --> 07:39.750
Polly?

07:39.750 --> 07:41.792
I noticed it
a couple weeks ago.

07:41.792 --> 07:43.884
Now it smells
kind of funny.

07:43.884 --> 07:45.756
That is
one infected abscess.

07:45.756 --> 07:48.509
We're gonna have to
open that up.

07:48.509 --> 07:50.180
What are you doing?

07:50.180 --> 07:52.723
My patient needs an I&D
for his abscess.

07:52.723 --> 07:54.224
Yeah, not by you.
Page surgery.

07:54.224 --> 07:55.896
I am surgery.

07:55.896 --> 07:57.728
No, not in here you're not.
You do not lance,

07:57.728 --> 07:59.600
you do not drain,
you do not cut.

07:59.600 --> 08:01.061
Look,
it'll take five minutes.

08:01.061 --> 08:03.103
You are not authorized
to use a scalpel on anyone.

08:03.103 --> 08:04.565
Page surgery.

08:06.106 --> 08:07.568
I thought you said
you were a surgeon.

08:09.159 --> 08:11.491
[ Sighs ]

08:24.174 --> 08:25.505
I wanted to
let you know that

08:25.505 --> 08:28.178
the internal reports
have been completed and filed.

08:28.178 --> 08:29.760
Copies will be
mailed to you,

08:29.760 --> 08:32.052
and all your records
have gone to the D.A.

08:32.052 --> 08:33.303
Okay. Thanks.

08:33.303 --> 08:35.055
Uh, one more thing.

08:35.055 --> 08:38.308
While the legal proceedings
are still ongoing,

08:38.308 --> 08:41.481
you are not
to discuss this matter

08:41.481 --> 08:42.903
within the walls
of this hospital.

08:42.903 --> 08:45.025
Don't talk about it
to anyone.

08:45.025 --> 08:46.907
-Understood?
-Yeah, I understand.

08:48.989 --> 08:50.360
You know, it won't be hard
not to talk about it

08:50.360 --> 08:52.653
'cause no one talks to me much
now anyways, so...

08:58.709 --> 09:00.871
You know, Dr. Avery's being
called in as an expert, I think.

09:00.871 --> 09:02.663
DeLuca,
what'd I just say?

09:02.663 --> 09:05.255
Right.
Don't talk to anyone.

09:05.255 --> 09:07.427
Got it.

09:08.298 --> 09:10.220
[ Sighs ]

09:10.220 --> 09:11.802
Pan scan with contrast,
please.

09:14.344 --> 09:16.096
How old was I
when my dad died?

09:16.096 --> 09:17.888
Sorry?

09:17.888 --> 09:19.059
How old was I
when my dad died?

09:19.059 --> 09:20.891
-5.
-I was 5.

09:20.891 --> 09:22.813
See, you knew that.

09:22.813 --> 09:27.397
But your dad died, too,
and I have no idea when or how.

09:27.397 --> 09:29.740
It hasn't come up.

09:29.740 --> 09:32.032
Well, don't you think
it should have?

09:32.032 --> 09:33.824
Or maybe we didn't
give it enough time to.

09:33.824 --> 09:36.406
We gave ourselves
a two-week engagement.

09:36.406 --> 09:38.078
I think we're okay.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.250
I think I should know how old
you were when your father died.

09:40.250 --> 09:41.411
-It's -- [ Sighs ]
-Almost 10.

09:41.411 --> 09:43.503
-Ah.
-He knows?

09:43.503 --> 09:46.296
[ Sighs ]

09:46.296 --> 09:48.088
Hey, sorry.

09:48.088 --> 09:49.379
[ Chuckles ]

09:49.379 --> 09:52.052
What? It's not a secret, is it?
-No.

09:52.052 --> 09:53.053
-Was that a secret?
-No, no.

09:53.053 --> 09:55.055
It's just she's worried
about stuff

09:55.055 --> 09:56.556
she doesn't need to
be worried about.

09:56.556 --> 10:00.520
Makes it a little more difficult
than it needs to be, right?

10:00.520 --> 10:02.312
Yeah,
it's worth it, though.

10:02.312 --> 10:04.354
Definitely.

10:07.988 --> 10:09.029
Scans up?

10:09.029 --> 10:11.281
Nope. Just started.

10:14.655 --> 10:17.237
Oh, you're back.
I didn't know you were here.

10:17.237 --> 10:19.329
I'm not back.

10:19.329 --> 10:23.834
I'm here early for my
appointment with Dr. Robbins.

10:23.834 --> 10:25.836
Six hours early.

10:25.836 --> 10:28.378
Baby's in the nursery,
so I'm here to finally sleep.

10:28.378 --> 10:29.840
Dibs on bottom bunk.

10:29.840 --> 10:33.173
Don't you have a bed of your own
at home?

10:33.173 --> 10:35.215
Not my home.

10:35.215 --> 10:38.258
I can't day nap there
'cause it's cleaning day,

10:38.258 --> 10:41.601
and people are vacuuming
and polishing.

10:41.601 --> 10:43.814
It would feel rude.

10:43.814 --> 10:45.856
You're making
very little sense.

10:45.856 --> 10:48.608
You know that thing
they say about

10:48.608 --> 10:51.191
how you're supposed to sleep
when the baby sleeps?

10:51.191 --> 10:52.983
That's a lie!

10:52.983 --> 10:54.404
Babies don't sleep.

10:54.404 --> 10:56.616
-I'd like to sleep.
-At least my baby doesn't.

10:56.616 --> 10:58.779
Except when she does sleep,
then I don't sleep.

10:58.779 --> 11:00.540
-You know why?
-'Cause you keep talking to her.

11:00.540 --> 11:03.623
Because I am a guest
in Jackson's house.

11:03.623 --> 11:05.876
And Kepners
are perfect guests,

11:05.876 --> 11:08.338
and being
a perfect guest...

11:08.338 --> 11:10.000
is a hard job.

11:10.000 --> 11:12.713
Listen, Dr. Kepner,
I empathize, I really do,

11:12.713 --> 11:16.556
but I just spent 16 hours
straight removing a meningioma

11:16.556 --> 11:20.680
and clipping something like a
million back-to-back aneurysms.

11:20.680 --> 11:22.973
And I'm back on Dr. Shepherd's
service in a couple of hours,

11:22.973 --> 11:25.265
so I need my sleep, too,

11:25.265 --> 11:27.567
so I could go cut into
actual human brains, so --

11:27.567 --> 11:29.269
[ Snoring ]

11:29.269 --> 11:30.861
You got to be kidding me.

11:32.072 --> 11:34.314
[ Sighs ]

11:35.575 --> 11:38.698
[ Indistinct conversations,
baby crying ]

11:38.698 --> 11:41.371
Well, am I dying?
Do I got the cancer?
No.

11:41.371 --> 11:44.034
Good news, Earl. Looks like
you just had beets for dinner.

11:44.034 --> 11:45.956
You're having a natural reaction
called beeturia.

11:45.956 --> 11:47.627
It's where the red pigment
of the beet passes through --

11:47.627 --> 11:48.829
Timir:
Which means you're fine.

11:48.829 --> 11:50.831
Give this to the desk
on your way out.

11:50.831 --> 11:52.963
This is a clinic,
not a hotel.

11:52.963 --> 11:55.635
Bed six -- binge drinker.
Her name's Emma.

11:55.635 --> 11:58.098
Frequent flier -- in here
once a month. Good luck.

11:58.098 --> 12:00.680
Uh, what's the protocol
for underage alcoholics?

12:00.680 --> 12:02.432
Uh, like an adult.
You hydrate her,

12:02.432 --> 12:03.974
give her the pamphlet,
then get her out.

12:03.974 --> 12:05.145
We need the bed.

12:05.145 --> 12:08.268
[ Sighs ]

12:09.609 --> 12:11.611
[ Sighs ] Finally.

12:11.611 --> 12:13.523
Emma, right?
How you feeling today?

12:13.523 --> 12:16.486
Oh, I'm feeling amazing.
I'm feeling perfect.

12:16.486 --> 12:17.778
Got it all together.

12:17.778 --> 12:19.319
I'm Kendall
and Khloé and Kylie

12:19.319 --> 12:20.861
and whatever other
"K" names you got.

12:20.861 --> 12:22.953
Just give me an I.V. bag,
and I'll be on my way.

12:22.953 --> 12:24.915
Headache, nausea, chills,
the spins --

12:24.915 --> 12:26.957
-I.V. bag.
-All right, vitals first

12:26.957 --> 12:28.498
then I decide what to give you,
okay?

12:28.498 --> 12:31.131
Oh, ew.
You're new.

12:31.131 --> 12:32.712
Put the I.V.
in the left arm.

12:32.712 --> 12:34.044
It's where
the good veins are.

12:34.044 --> 12:35.836
Start with a liter of saline
and push it hard.

12:35.836 --> 12:37.177
I'm dehydrated.

12:37.177 --> 12:38.548
And do me a favor.

12:38.548 --> 12:40.881
If you're an intern
or, like, dumb,

12:40.881 --> 12:43.343
get help, because last time,
I was poked about 100 times

12:43.343 --> 12:44.845
and my arm was purple
for weeks.

12:44.845 --> 12:46.977
That's good to know.

12:46.977 --> 12:48.188
How are the scans?

12:48.188 --> 12:50.020
Well, it looks like
a grade-3 splenic injury.

12:50.020 --> 12:51.601
How's the husband?
-He's worried about her.

12:51.601 --> 12:53.313
Mm. I'm gonna take her up
for an ex lap.

12:53.313 --> 12:55.946
For that? There's no reason.
There's no active bleeding.

12:55.946 --> 12:57.107
Well, I thought that,
too, but look.

12:57.107 --> 12:59.279
There's stranding and fullness
around the aorta.

12:59.279 --> 13:00.660
If we go in for the spleen,

13:00.660 --> 13:02.112
then we get to have a better
look when we're there.

13:02.112 --> 13:04.534
Right, but there's no
clinical reason for surgery.

13:04.534 --> 13:07.868
Well, there is if we find out
that her aorta is in trouble.

13:07.868 --> 13:11.411
If. That's my point.
We should wait and see.

13:11.411 --> 13:13.753
I can see what you mean, Hunt,
but Grey's right.

13:13.753 --> 13:15.375
I mean,
the patient is stable.

13:15.375 --> 13:17.547
Observation just makes
more sense right now.

13:17.547 --> 13:19.589
We do a repeat C.T. angio
in a few hours --

13:19.589 --> 13:21.381
Oh, waiting is definitely
the safer choice.

13:21.381 --> 13:22.592
Well, I disagree.

13:27.687 --> 13:29.479
Oh, so that's it, then?

13:29.479 --> 13:30.770
Two against one?

13:30.770 --> 13:32.062
Fine.

13:32.062 --> 13:33.693
She gets checks
every 30 minutes,

13:33.693 --> 13:35.145
and I hope you're both right.

13:35.145 --> 13:37.938
♪♪

13:41.401 --> 13:42.943
We make quite the team.

13:42.943 --> 13:44.824
I don't need a team.
It's the right call.

13:44.824 --> 13:46.496
This is the wrong call.

13:46.496 --> 13:49.209
You got outvoted
by two smart surgeons.

13:49.209 --> 13:50.290
It happens.

13:52.792 --> 13:54.714
So, why did you join
the army?

13:54.714 --> 13:56.046
Okay,
why are we doing this?

13:56.046 --> 13:57.217
I feel like
I'm in a job interview.

13:57.217 --> 13:59.759
There's just stuff I don't know.
I mean, it's scary.

13:59.759 --> 14:01.922
We have
our whole lives to --

14:01.922 --> 14:04.264
And there's stuff that
you don't know about me.

14:04.264 --> 14:06.176
And what
if you don't like it?

14:06.176 --> 14:08.018
What if it's too scary?

14:08.018 --> 14:10.730
How bad could it be?

14:10.730 --> 14:13.603
Hey, hey, really.
How bad?

14:15.896 --> 14:17.397
You know what?

14:17.397 --> 14:18.478
Never mind.

14:18.478 --> 14:20.320
It's fine.

14:30.790 --> 14:32.202
When the trocar's in
the amniotic cavity,

14:32.202 --> 14:33.623
that's when we use
a fetoscope -- Hey, DeLuca.

14:33.623 --> 14:35.755
Come here.

14:35.755 --> 14:37.797
Freeze.

14:37.797 --> 14:39.299
Tilt your head up.

14:39.299 --> 14:41.051
Chin up. Turn.

14:41.051 --> 14:42.462
Damn.

14:42.462 --> 14:43.593
It's beautiful.

14:43.593 --> 14:44.764
You look nice today, too.

14:44.764 --> 14:46.676
[ Chuckles ]
Avery did a really great job.

14:46.676 --> 14:48.468
Nice symmetrical
eye sockets.

14:48.468 --> 14:49.849
Not even a hint of
residual bruising.

14:49.849 --> 14:52.312
No scars.
How are you feeling?

14:52.312 --> 14:53.853
-I'm fine.
-Yeah?

14:53.853 --> 14:55.435
I keep missing you
at home.

14:55.435 --> 14:57.938
Avery give you
a clean bill of health?
Yeah, no, I-I'm good.

14:57.938 --> 14:59.479
And what about the trial?
Any news of a court date?

14:59.479 --> 15:01.111
-I can't really talk about it.
-Whoa, whoa, whoa.

15:01.111 --> 15:02.902
What are you talking about,
you can't talk about it?

15:02.902 --> 15:04.734
We share a bathroom.
-With anyone.

15:04.734 --> 15:06.446
Okay, it's the Chief's orders.
I'm sorry.

15:10.330 --> 15:11.741
Bed six, Karev.

15:11.741 --> 15:13.333
I have to
check on this guy.

15:17.167 --> 15:19.629
Okay, uh, so I have
two more patients' parents

15:19.629 --> 15:21.131
saying they'll be
character witnesses.

15:21.131 --> 15:22.542
Yeah.

15:22.542 --> 15:24.254
I-I'm trying to get there.

15:24.254 --> 15:25.465
I-I'll be there.

15:25.465 --> 15:27.257
I'll -- I'll try.

15:27.257 --> 15:28.428
Was that your lawyer?

15:28.428 --> 15:29.509
Meeting's supposed to
be at 4:00

15:29.509 --> 15:32.182
if I can get past
Timir the gatekeeper.

15:32.182 --> 15:34.104
You bring ketchup?
-Ugh, did you wash your hands?

15:37.477 --> 15:39.019
Why are we here?

15:39.019 --> 15:40.770
Oh, because Alex is here,

15:40.770 --> 15:43.233
and we want to see
what Alex is up to.

15:43.233 --> 15:45.365
Does Alex have something he'd
like to share with the group?

15:45.365 --> 15:46.446
AA pamphlets?

15:46.446 --> 15:48.448
They're for this patient,
this college kid.

15:48.448 --> 15:50.870
She's a mess.
-Literature is not gonna do it.

15:50.870 --> 15:52.072
When you're addicted
to something

15:52.072 --> 15:54.494
and you want it so badly,
a piece of paper is --

15:54.494 --> 15:55.785
It's not gonna
make her stay away.

15:55.785 --> 15:57.287
What would
make you stay away?

15:57.287 --> 16:00.290
Say if you were a bartender
and an alcoholic

16:00.290 --> 16:02.672
and there's alcohol
in front of you

16:02.672 --> 16:04.424
right under your nose
all the time.

16:04.424 --> 16:06.466
Doing cardio surgeries.

16:06.466 --> 16:08.138
Uh, count to five.

16:08.138 --> 16:09.799
If that doesn't work,
get out of there,

16:09.799 --> 16:12.182
remove yourself
from the situation.

16:12.182 --> 16:15.095
So, on a scale of
lots to nothing,

16:15.095 --> 16:17.227
how much would you say
you knew about my brother

16:17.227 --> 16:18.438
when you guys
got married?

16:18.438 --> 16:19.899
I'm not getting
in the middle of that.

16:19.899 --> 16:21.941
Why? Did Owen...

16:21.941 --> 16:24.404
I knew Owen would
say something to you.

16:24.404 --> 16:26.196
See? There's something
you know about him.

16:26.196 --> 16:29.109
-Uh, back to my patient.
-Your kid might need an ally.

16:29.109 --> 16:32.202
Someone who's been there
who can speak the language.

16:32.202 --> 16:34.824
A pamphlet's not gonna do it.
Not that I am offering.

16:34.824 --> 16:35.955
I have my own stuff
going on.

16:38.038 --> 16:41.881
Really?
This is not a cafeteria, Karev.

16:41.881 --> 16:43.213
We've got two cases of strep,
your alcoholic.

16:43.213 --> 16:44.794
Your foot guy still
needs his foot done.

16:44.794 --> 16:46.176
I paged surgery!

16:46.176 --> 16:48.928
You're in a room
full of surgeons.

16:48.928 --> 16:51.721
One of you guys want to lance
a patient's foot abscess for me?

16:51.721 --> 16:53.133
-Resident's job.
-I'm eating.

16:53.133 --> 16:54.594
I would,
but I don't want to.

16:56.766 --> 16:59.729
Yeah.
I'm gonna pay for that.

17:03.733 --> 17:05.355
How much longer?

17:05.355 --> 17:06.906
The I.V.'s
still almost full,

17:06.906 --> 17:09.449
and I don't have time
to sit here all day.

17:09.449 --> 17:11.281
Hello?
I have work.

17:11.281 --> 17:13.323
-Call in sick.
-I can't call in.

17:13.323 --> 17:16.246
Just tell me if I'm looking
at 20 minutes or an hour or...

17:18.158 --> 17:21.040
Oh, my God,
I'm not an alcoholic!

17:21.040 --> 17:22.712
They say you're in here
all the time asking for fluids.

17:22.712 --> 17:24.834
Because I've figured out
what makes my body feel better.

17:24.834 --> 17:26.756
Isn't that what
doctors should want?

17:26.756 --> 17:28.298
I'm making
your life easier.

17:28.298 --> 17:30.760
Fine, forget it.

17:31.671 --> 17:33.263
You know what?

17:33.263 --> 17:34.764
You're full of crap.

17:34.764 --> 17:36.476
-Excuse me?
-Look, I may be a doctor,

17:36.476 --> 17:38.057
but that doesn't mean
I never partied before.

17:38.057 --> 17:39.809
-I had one beer.
-Oh, come on.

17:39.809 --> 17:41.181
You're a kid who routinely
comes in here for an I.V.

17:41.181 --> 17:42.852
after a night
of partying.

17:42.852 --> 17:45.315
And you're an adult
who routinely uses
"party" as a verb.

17:45.315 --> 17:47.527
-Emma, listen to me.
-You're not listening to me.

17:47.527 --> 17:50.280
Emma, you keep doing this and
an I.V. isn't your fix anymore.
Oh, my God.

17:50.280 --> 17:52.452
Because first it's drinking,
then someone gives you a pill.

17:52.452 --> 17:54.194
Next it's needles.

17:54.194 --> 17:56.156
Before you know it,
you're out on the street
with all the other junkies.

17:56.156 --> 17:57.537
Is that how
you want it to go?

17:57.537 --> 17:59.579
No!
On the side of the road
covered in your own puke?

17:59.579 --> 18:00.790
Richard: Dr. Karev.

18:03.203 --> 18:04.964
That's enough.

18:04.964 --> 18:07.006
Okay, listen,
this girl's a drunk.
No, I'm not!

18:07.006 --> 18:09.759
Step away from that young woman
right now.

18:09.759 --> 18:12.802
♪♪

18:19.018 --> 18:20.810
[ Whispering ]
That was good.

18:20.810 --> 18:22.101
It was very good.
Very convincing.

18:22.101 --> 18:24.224
[ Whispering ] Yeah?
I think I was a little harsh.

18:24.224 --> 18:26.186
Ah, it was just right.

18:26.186 --> 18:28.938
You were a jerk.
She and I have a common enemy.

18:28.938 --> 18:30.570
How much time do I have?

18:30.570 --> 18:31.611
About half an hour.

18:31.611 --> 18:32.822
I slowed down
her I.V. drip.

18:32.822 --> 18:34.033
Smart.

18:34.033 --> 18:35.575
I'm going in.

18:38.828 --> 18:40.870
Good luck.

18:42.582 --> 18:44.164
Oh, sorry.

18:44.164 --> 18:46.706
I-I didn't realize, um --

18:46.706 --> 18:48.838
I'll just go
to another room.

18:48.838 --> 18:50.420
You don't have to.
I'm almost done.

18:50.420 --> 18:52.051
Okay, great.

18:56.926 --> 18:59.179
Four, five.

19:00.930 --> 19:03.062
Five what?

19:03.062 --> 19:05.024
More minutes.

19:05.024 --> 19:06.436
Yeah.

19:06.436 --> 19:08.318
Uh, oh, you know what?
I'll come back.

19:08.318 --> 19:09.899
You don't have to.

19:12.111 --> 19:14.073
So, Polly doesn't
need surgery?

19:14.073 --> 19:16.946
Right now, no.
It's a waiting game.

19:16.946 --> 19:19.449
We would like to wait and see
if it resolves itself,

19:19.449 --> 19:22.242
but she's stable and awake.

19:22.242 --> 19:23.453
She'll hate this.

19:23.453 --> 19:25.625
Waiting and seeing.

19:25.625 --> 19:27.787
When I got hurt,
we were engaged,

19:27.787 --> 19:30.500
and I gave her an out.

19:30.500 --> 19:32.842
I mean,
it only seemed fair.

19:32.842 --> 19:35.845
Her answer was to haul
the chaplain into my room.

19:35.845 --> 19:37.927
We basically eloped
in a hospital.

19:37.927 --> 19:39.889
Nothing gets to her.

19:39.889 --> 19:41.100
I like her.

19:41.100 --> 19:43.433
Except glider planes.
Those are my thing.

19:43.433 --> 19:44.894
She thinks she hides it,

19:44.894 --> 19:47.066
but I know she's not wild
about heights.

19:47.066 --> 19:50.019
Oh, God.
I hope she's okay.

19:50.019 --> 19:51.651
I'm gonna let her know
you're here, okay?

19:54.073 --> 19:55.405
Hey, Polly.

19:55.405 --> 19:56.906
Someone's here to see you.

19:56.906 --> 19:58.528
[ Coughing ]

20:01.781 --> 20:03.243
[ Grunts ]

20:03.243 --> 20:04.704
I need some help in here!

20:04.704 --> 20:06.456
-What's happening to her?
-Abdomen's rigid.

20:06.456 --> 20:08.087
Belly's full of blood.
Hang two units.

20:08.087 --> 20:10.830
I need a 7-0 E.T. tube
and an intubation tray.

20:10.830 --> 20:12.131
Blood's on the infuser.
Coags sent.

20:12.131 --> 20:14.504
Page Hunt and Riggs
and book an O.R. right now.

20:14.504 --> 20:15.675
You said she was stable.

20:33.022 --> 20:34.444
What the hell's going on?

20:34.444 --> 20:36.816
Her spleen ruptured,
and now her aorta's dissecting.

20:36.816 --> 20:38.157
Gown us.
We could've avoided this.

20:38.157 --> 20:39.319
Yeah, well,
this shouldn't have happened.

20:39.319 --> 20:41.160
It wouldn't have if you two
hadn't teamed up against me,

20:41.160 --> 20:43.363
if we hadn't waited!
Okay, listen,
can we do this another time,

20:43.363 --> 20:44.954
because if we don't
get to this dissection,

20:44.954 --> 20:46.035
it's gonna take out
her coronaries.

20:46.035 --> 20:47.627
Let's get in here.
I need some hands.

20:51.501 --> 20:55.755
I told that other doctor
this is just what my body does.

20:55.755 --> 20:58.468
I have a beer
or I get dehydrated,

20:58.468 --> 21:00.179
and I get sick.

21:00.179 --> 21:02.181
I know how to fix it.
This is how I fix it.

21:02.181 --> 21:04.183
I totally understand.

21:04.183 --> 21:05.805
You know your own body
better than anyone.

21:05.805 --> 21:07.347
Exactly!
And I don't need some idiot

21:07.347 --> 21:09.389
telling me I have a problem
when I don't.

21:09.389 --> 21:11.731
Okay, you know how to handle it.
You know your own limits.

21:11.731 --> 21:14.273
It's doctors like him
that are the problem.

21:14.273 --> 21:16.396
He thinks
I'm some crazy party girl.

21:16.396 --> 21:17.947
I'm not an alcoholic.

21:17.947 --> 21:19.609
You know,
I used to tell myself that.

21:19.609 --> 21:21.861
Well,
actually quite a bit.

21:21.861 --> 21:24.163
We talked a lot about that
in AA.

21:24.163 --> 21:26.366
AA?

21:26.366 --> 21:28.328
Really? What is this?

21:28.328 --> 21:30.960
Are you trying to play good cop,
bad cop with me or something?

21:30.960 --> 21:32.962
Emma, no, no, no.
All I'm trying to --

21:32.962 --> 21:34.504
I am not stupid and I won't
stick around for this.

21:34.504 --> 21:36.255
What --
-No, thanks.

21:36.255 --> 21:37.967
[ Arm cracks ]
-Emma, wait a minute.
-[ Screams ]

21:37.967 --> 21:39.128
Alex: What did you do?

21:39.128 --> 21:40.720
I-I-I just barely
touched her.

21:40.720 --> 21:42.472
Emma -- Emma,
just calm down.

21:42.472 --> 21:43.763
Don't touch me!

21:43.763 --> 21:46.596
Just --
Just let me fix it.

21:48.267 --> 21:49.809
[ Arm cracks ]

21:52.231 --> 21:53.393
Oh, my God.

21:53.393 --> 21:56.396
Oh. What on earth?

21:56.396 --> 21:59.278
So...
can I get out of here now?

22:02.532 --> 22:04.243
Who is responsible
for this?

22:04.243 --> 22:05.655
Not the clinic.
It's Karev's fault.

22:05.655 --> 22:06.946
He should've
discharged her.

22:06.946 --> 22:08.327
Dr. Karev works for
the clinic.

22:08.327 --> 22:09.949
Dr. Weber,
did you injure her?

22:09.949 --> 22:11.290
Because now it's a liability.

22:11.290 --> 22:12.712
She appears fine.

22:12.712 --> 22:14.504
She needs x-rays
to rule out a fracture.

22:14.504 --> 22:17.667
Well, she's back in bed
and not happy about it.

22:17.667 --> 22:18.918
I'll check on
those x-rays.

22:18.918 --> 22:20.460
Mm.

22:20.460 --> 22:23.342
Actually, Chief, uh,
I could use a little help.

22:23.342 --> 22:24.964
I have a meeting with my lawyer
this afternoon,

22:24.964 --> 22:26.466
and Timir won't let me out.

22:26.466 --> 22:28.428
I have helped you.
I got you this job.

22:28.428 --> 22:29.889
I didn't have to.

22:29.889 --> 22:31.310
What, you need me to help you
do that, too?

22:31.310 --> 22:33.352
Figure it out.

22:33.352 --> 22:35.354
[ Davie's "Whispers" plays ]

22:35.354 --> 22:37.356
Rush on these, please.
Thanks.

22:37.356 --> 22:39.399
♪ Voices in my head ♪

22:39.399 --> 22:44.534
So, Bailey told me, too,
not to say anything to anybody.

22:44.534 --> 22:46.786
But, uh...

22:46.786 --> 22:49.489
I don't have anyone else
who understands except you,

22:49.489 --> 22:52.291
and I know that Bailey said
not to say anything,

22:52.291 --> 22:54.373
but it's like --
Oh, heads up.

22:54.373 --> 22:56.165
Uh, I --
-I-I'm gonna go --

22:56.165 --> 22:57.547
Okay. Oh.

23:00.049 --> 23:01.461
♪ All I hear is whispers ♪

23:01.461 --> 23:03.633
April grinds the coffee?

23:03.633 --> 23:04.844
And brews it.

23:04.844 --> 23:06.385
Every morning.

23:06.385 --> 23:07.967
Yeah,
I don't see the problem.

23:07.967 --> 23:10.009
No matter how late
we are up with Harriet,

23:10.009 --> 23:12.101
she wakes up before me
and makes the coffee.

23:12.101 --> 23:14.393
No matter how badly I need
to leave and go to work or --

23:14.393 --> 23:16.015
Yeah, but you can't just walk
away from a fresh pot of coffee.

23:16.015 --> 23:17.897
And not feel like an ass,
no.

23:17.897 --> 23:20.980
So, I drink the coffee
and make the small talk

23:20.980 --> 23:22.361
because that's what people do,
apparently,

23:22.361 --> 23:23.823
but sometimes I don't want to
make the small talk.

23:23.823 --> 23:25.234
What are you laughing at?

23:25.234 --> 23:27.527
[ Chuckling ] Nothing, man.
I just -- I-I remember.

23:27.527 --> 23:29.699
From when you stayed
with me and Miranda.

23:29.699 --> 23:31.160
Yeah,
but I wasn't that bad.

23:31.160 --> 23:32.492
Dude.

23:32.492 --> 23:34.834
I was?

23:34.834 --> 23:37.587
No. You --
You should've said something.

23:37.587 --> 23:39.378
Yes,
and so should you.

23:39.378 --> 23:40.800
Just talk to April.

23:40.800 --> 23:43.042
Yeah, I -- Okay, you're right.
I will.

23:43.042 --> 23:45.044
It wasn't really that bad
with me, though, right?

23:45.044 --> 23:46.546
It might've been better
if you'd have

23:46.546 --> 23:48.638
brewed a brother a cup of coffee
every now and again, but...

23:49.889 --> 23:52.181
I'm so tired.

23:52.181 --> 23:55.725
But I go out of my way to make
coffee every morning to be nice.

23:55.725 --> 23:57.396
So sleep in.
Don't make coffee.

23:57.396 --> 23:58.898
Well,
I have to do something.

23:58.898 --> 24:00.860
I was taught to be
a courteous guest.

24:00.860 --> 24:02.151
But you're not a guest.

24:02.151 --> 24:04.323
You're a --
You're a co-habitant.

24:04.323 --> 24:07.567
You're a roommate.
He's your -- He's your Andrew.

24:07.567 --> 24:10.199
[ Chuckles ]
He's not my Andrew, no.

24:10.199 --> 24:14.744
He's my ex, and we live together
'cause he's being nice,

24:14.744 --> 24:18.127
so I need to be a good
houseguest even if it kills me,

24:18.127 --> 24:20.750
which it might, unless I die
of lack of sleep first.

24:20.750 --> 24:23.543
I can't handle
dying right now.

24:23.543 --> 24:25.214
So move out.

24:25.214 --> 24:26.886
-What?
-Your incision is healed.

24:26.886 --> 24:29.719
You can lift as much as
you want, so come back to work,

24:29.719 --> 24:31.851
move out of the house,
and then do whatever you want.

24:31.851 --> 24:35.014
Doctor's orders.

24:35.014 --> 24:37.807
Not only do you get
dumped on me in my clinic,

24:37.807 --> 24:39.398
but then you make me look
incompetent

24:39.398 --> 24:41.060
in front of the Chief?

24:41.060 --> 24:42.191
I didn't do anything.

24:42.191 --> 24:44.273
You pulled a girl's arm
out of her socket.

24:44.273 --> 24:46.816
Yeah, and I put it back
like I always do,

24:46.816 --> 24:48.107
so when can I go?

24:48.107 --> 24:49.609
You still need to
get x-rays.

24:49.609 --> 24:50.910
And I didn't even touch her.
-You upset her.

24:50.910 --> 24:52.161
You're the reason
she tried to leave.

24:52.161 --> 24:53.993
Look, my shift
starts really soon.

24:53.993 --> 24:56.876
You have no idea,
but my boss is the biggest jerk.

24:56.876 --> 24:59.328
I have some idea.
All it takes is
her filing one complaint.

24:59.328 --> 25:02.041
I know you don't care 'cause you
have a cushy job to go back to,

25:02.041 --> 25:03.833
but this is my cushy job.

25:03.833 --> 25:05.174
I don't need you
causing trouble.

25:05.174 --> 25:06.756
You paged me?

25:09.128 --> 25:12.471
Can you hear me, Karev?
Are you even paying attention?

25:12.471 --> 25:13.803
I, uh, paged surgery.

25:13.803 --> 25:15.344
I need a consult
over an abscess.

25:15.344 --> 25:17.016
Okay.

25:17.016 --> 25:19.098
Bed two.
Can you do it?

25:19.098 --> 25:21.230
You paged me here
to do your scut?

25:21.230 --> 25:22.642
No, no, that's not --

25:22.642 --> 25:24.644
Then why else do you need me
to lance a boil?

25:25.735 --> 25:27.737
Because
I'm not allowed to.

25:27.737 --> 25:29.408
Damn right,
you are not allowed to,

25:29.408 --> 25:31.530
and -- and you're not allowed to
go near that girl again either.

25:31.530 --> 25:32.992
Okay, I don't want you
anywhere near her.

25:32.992 --> 25:35.204
Screw it. Screw all this!
There are your patients.

25:35.204 --> 25:37.156
There's your surgical consult.
I have someplace to be.

25:37.156 --> 25:39.579
♪♪

26:04.443 --> 26:06.105
Hold on! Stop the bus!

26:13.152 --> 26:14.573
I got your message.
What's so urgent?
Check it out.

26:14.573 --> 26:16.575
So you know how Emma
presented with a hangover
but insisted that wasn't it?

26:16.575 --> 26:17.827
Yeah, even though
she was in the clinic

26:17.827 --> 26:19.498
every couple weeks
for I.V. hydration?

26:19.498 --> 26:21.540
And she said that thing with her
arms has happened to her before.

26:21.540 --> 26:22.872
Well, what's this
have to do with me?

26:22.872 --> 26:24.964
Well, just read the chart.
Look at her list of symptoms.

26:24.964 --> 26:26.085
I mean, there's something
wrong with her,

26:26.085 --> 26:28.007
but she's not an alcoholic.

26:28.007 --> 26:31.420
Dehydration, bruises easy,
joint hyper mobility --

26:31.420 --> 26:33.092
that's for sure.

26:33.092 --> 26:34.844
Fainting spe--

26:37.176 --> 26:38.638
Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome?

26:38.638 --> 26:40.179
You're not as strong
as you think.

26:40.179 --> 26:43.022
I only encountered
a couple cases in my career.

26:43.022 --> 26:45.104
I mean, we'll have to run tests
to confirm it.

26:45.104 --> 26:49.188
But if you're right
and she has this...

26:49.188 --> 26:51.901
Karev, you may have just
saved this girl's life.

26:51.901 --> 26:53.783
Did you tell her?

26:53.783 --> 26:55.865
No,
that's why I paged you.

26:55.865 --> 26:57.236
You have to tell her,
not me.

26:57.236 --> 26:59.578
Look, if I give her
some big diagnosis,

26:59.578 --> 27:01.450
I'm undermining
Timir's authority,
but if you tell her --

27:01.450 --> 27:03.002
No, it doesn't seem right.
No.

27:03.002 --> 27:05.705
Look, she needs this way more
than I need a credit.

27:15.134 --> 27:17.596
If we can't catheterize through
the inferior petrosal sinus,

27:17.596 --> 27:19.809
will we go straight to
the superior ophthalmic
vein or what?

27:19.809 --> 27:20.890
What?

27:20.890 --> 27:22.601
You...

27:22.601 --> 27:24.263
had sickle cell anemia.

27:24.263 --> 27:26.065
Oh, good. This.

27:26.065 --> 27:28.768
Have?
Had? Have had?

27:28.768 --> 27:30.940
-Had.
-You had that.

27:30.940 --> 27:32.692
I know that about you.

27:32.692 --> 27:34.694
Nobody knows that about you,
but you told me,

27:34.694 --> 27:36.906
trusted me
with the information.

27:36.906 --> 27:39.198
You let me know you.
I know that about you.

27:39.198 --> 27:40.950
I know
we are about to go treat

27:40.950 --> 27:42.992
a dural carotid
cavernous fistula.

27:42.992 --> 27:44.663
Owen could've had it, too.
I have no idea.

27:44.663 --> 27:46.085
Unlikely
for a number of reasons.

27:46.085 --> 27:47.707
But I know it about you,

27:47.707 --> 27:50.710
just like I know that
you do not like dogs.

27:50.710 --> 27:54.003
You don't ever go to church.
You do like mushrooms.

27:54.003 --> 27:56.465
And I knew all of those things
before today.

27:56.465 --> 27:58.888
I should've married you.

27:58.888 --> 28:01.680
I'm not sure that would've
worked out for either of us.

28:01.680 --> 28:03.222
That church one
is just a guess.

28:06.265 --> 28:07.727
Okay, wait.

28:07.727 --> 28:09.358
You're gonna have to
say that all again.

28:09.358 --> 28:11.110
Ellie what-is-it
syndrome?

28:11.110 --> 28:13.072
Ehlers-Danlos.

28:13.072 --> 28:17.156
It's extremely hard to diagnose,
but all your symptoms add up.

28:17.156 --> 28:18.447
You did a great job

28:18.447 --> 28:20.369
paying attention
to what your body needs.

28:20.369 --> 28:21.450
[ Crying ]

28:21.450 --> 28:24.203
This diagnosis is a good thing,
Emma.

28:24.203 --> 28:26.325
We now know better
how to actually help you.

28:26.325 --> 28:27.877
All this time...

28:27.877 --> 28:29.708
[ Sighs ]

28:29.708 --> 28:31.831
So, this means it's real.

28:31.831 --> 28:34.213
I'm not overreacting.
I'm not crazy.

28:34.213 --> 28:35.795
Definitely not.

28:35.795 --> 28:38.047
Thank you, Dr. Weber.

28:38.047 --> 28:39.218
[ Sniffles ]

28:39.218 --> 28:41.470
There's no way
that other asshat doctor

28:41.470 --> 28:43.052
would've figured this out.

28:43.052 --> 28:45.224
That's why the clinic's here,
Emma.

28:45.224 --> 28:46.605
We're just happy to help.

28:46.605 --> 28:48.347
[ Sniffles ]

28:48.347 --> 28:50.189
Thank you.

28:50.189 --> 28:51.771
[ Exhales deeply ]

28:59.158 --> 29:00.569
While we were in there,

29:00.569 --> 29:02.571
you had a sudden dissection
in your aorta,

29:02.571 --> 29:04.824
which, um, well, I'm glad
we caught it in time.

29:04.824 --> 29:06.035
How you feeling?

29:06.035 --> 29:07.326
I don't know.

29:07.326 --> 29:09.458
I -- I guess, like --

29:09.458 --> 29:12.501
like I fell out of the sky in
a plane I never wanted to be in.

29:12.501 --> 29:14.543
Don't tell Danny
I said that.
No.

29:14.543 --> 29:16.715
He'll feel so bad.
I know him.

29:16.715 --> 29:19.178
He's eating himself alive
over this.

29:19.178 --> 29:20.179
Can I see him?

29:20.179 --> 29:21.881
Yeah.
I'll find him for you.

29:21.881 --> 29:24.343
Oh, one more thing
that's kind of strange.

29:24.343 --> 29:26.015
I can't feel my legs yet.

29:26.015 --> 29:27.686
When is this anesthesia
gonna wear off?

29:27.686 --> 29:30.149
What?

29:30.149 --> 29:31.891
So, when the aorta
dissected,

29:31.891 --> 29:34.063
it compromised
the feeder vessels

29:34.063 --> 29:37.026
to the spinal cord
right around L-4.

29:37.026 --> 29:39.738
And it damaged
the cord there.

29:39.738 --> 29:42.361
So, she's paralyzed
from the waist down?

29:42.361 --> 29:43.742
And it's irreversible.

29:43.742 --> 29:45.454
If we'd been
in there sooner --

29:45.454 --> 29:47.286
It wouldn't have
made a difference.
Yes, if we had gone in --

29:47.286 --> 29:48.457
Owen, it wouldn't have
made a difference!

29:48.457 --> 29:50.039
It dissected
right in front of us!

29:50.039 --> 29:51.831
I couldn't have foreseen that
and neither could you.

29:51.831 --> 29:53.462
This happens.

29:53.462 --> 29:55.754
It's happened to me
before.

29:55.754 --> 29:57.336
Okay? It's unfortunate,
but it does.

29:57.336 --> 29:58.757
You couldn't have
saved this.

30:02.261 --> 30:03.222
I'll go tell her.

30:09.098 --> 30:10.599
That's the truth,
right?

30:10.599 --> 30:12.141
What?

30:12.141 --> 30:13.933
That we couldn't have
seen this coming.

30:13.933 --> 30:16.355
That's true?
-Why would you ask me that?

30:16.355 --> 30:18.277
Because I need to make sure
that our decision to wait

30:18.277 --> 30:20.199
didn't put this woman
in a wheelchair.

30:20.199 --> 30:21.490
No, it didn't.

30:21.490 --> 30:23.402
You didn't...

30:23.402 --> 30:26.495
side with me because of...

30:26.495 --> 30:27.706
you and I?

30:27.706 --> 30:29.578
Excuse me?

30:29.578 --> 30:32.912
Because we decided to wait,
this falls on us.
Whoa, whoa.

30:32.912 --> 30:35.584
If you think I would play around
with a patient's well-being

30:35.584 --> 30:37.046
in order
to get into your pants?

30:37.046 --> 30:39.258
That's not what I'm saying.
I'm asking a question.

30:39.258 --> 30:40.960
It's a damned
offensive question!

30:40.960 --> 30:44.763
Did we make the right decision
for the right reason?

30:44.763 --> 30:46.515
I agreed with you
because you were right,

30:46.515 --> 30:47.887
not because you were you.

30:47.887 --> 30:49.889
Now, what happened to Polly
is not to your fault.

30:49.889 --> 30:52.351
And it's certainly not mine.
I'm not that stupid!

30:52.351 --> 30:54.683
♪♪

31:13.122 --> 31:14.994
You heading home?

31:14.994 --> 31:17.296
I'm not sure I'm at liberty

31:17.296 --> 31:19.498
to disclose that information
at this time.

31:19.498 --> 31:21.210
Right.

31:21.210 --> 31:23.342
Wouldn't be prudent
at this juncture.
[ Chuckles ]

31:23.342 --> 31:25.004
Your whereabouts should
remain need-to-know.

31:25.004 --> 31:27.056
Mm.

31:27.056 --> 31:29.969
Look, if you can't
talk to anyone

31:29.969 --> 31:31.770
and I can't talk to anyone,

31:31.770 --> 31:34.273
no one's gonna know if
we talk to each other, right?

31:34.273 --> 31:37.316
True, yeah.

31:37.316 --> 31:39.648
You hungry?

31:39.648 --> 31:41.400
I better not say.

31:41.400 --> 31:43.362
[ Both chuckle ]

31:49.658 --> 31:52.371
So, Dr. Hunt says
that she's still groggy

31:52.371 --> 31:53.912
and trying to
process everything,

31:53.912 --> 31:55.414
but she wants to see you.

31:55.414 --> 31:57.586
I can't go in there.

31:57.586 --> 31:59.838
I can't. I-I'm the one
who did this to her.

31:59.838 --> 32:02.171
She's in the bed
because of me.

32:02.171 --> 32:04.133
I can't face her.
I can't go in.

32:04.133 --> 32:05.594
You have to.

32:05.594 --> 32:07.386
You're the only one she needs
right now.

32:07.386 --> 32:09.258
She was on the plane
because of me.

32:09.258 --> 32:12.681
And now she's off
and she's alive.

32:12.681 --> 32:14.683
Your wife is alive.

32:14.683 --> 32:17.436
And if there's anyone who could
tell her this isn't the end,

32:17.436 --> 32:19.148
that this isn't the worst thing
that could've happened,

32:19.148 --> 32:20.689
it's you.

32:20.689 --> 32:22.771
Because this isn't
the worst thing.

32:24.153 --> 32:25.824
She's still breathing.

32:25.824 --> 32:27.826
She needs you right now.

32:27.826 --> 32:31.620
She needs you to be strong
and pull it together for her.

32:31.620 --> 32:33.622
Daniel,
she's ready for you.

32:33.622 --> 32:37.416
But what --
what do I say?

32:37.416 --> 32:40.129
You guys love each other.

32:40.129 --> 32:41.630
You can say anything.

32:45.844 --> 32:48.257
[ Exhales deeply ]

32:48.257 --> 32:51.050
♪♪

33:09.608 --> 33:11.820
[ Door opens, keys jingle ]

33:11.820 --> 33:14.413
[ Whispering ]Shh.
She's finally sleeping.

33:14.413 --> 33:15.614
Jackson:
[ Whispering ] Okay.

33:15.614 --> 33:18.077
Shouldn't she be
in a crib or something?

33:18.077 --> 33:19.878
[ Sighs ]

33:19.878 --> 33:22.000
You should be happy
she's sleeping at all.

33:22.000 --> 33:24.503
Well, I mean,
I was hoping we could talk.

33:24.503 --> 33:26.585
Um, I just feel like
if I stop doing this,

33:26.585 --> 33:28.127
she's, like, gonna wake up.

33:28.127 --> 33:29.548
Okay. Totally fine.
It can wait.

33:29.548 --> 33:31.720
I'll just, um...

33:31.720 --> 33:33.092
I'll go watch the game
in my room.

33:33.092 --> 33:35.054
Did you want to
watch it in here,

33:35.054 --> 33:36.975
'cause I can try
to move her into her crib.

33:36.975 --> 33:38.597
No, it's totally fine.
Don't be silly.

33:38.597 --> 33:40.099
It's -- There's plenty of TVs.
It's fine.

33:40.099 --> 33:42.101
I mean, I'm aware,
but this one's the biggest.

33:42.101 --> 33:43.442
-I said no. Thank you.
-Are you sure you --

33:43.442 --> 33:45.274
'Cause if you want to watch
the game, like, I can --

33:45.274 --> 33:46.405
[ Normal voice ]
April, I said no.

33:46.405 --> 33:48.147
[ Normal voice ] Okay.

33:48.147 --> 33:51.029
I can't keep doing this.

33:51.029 --> 33:52.571
All right? I can't keep
walking on egg shells

33:52.571 --> 33:53.912
in my own house,
all right?

33:53.912 --> 33:56.705
We have to figure out a way
to freakin' exist together.

33:56.705 --> 33:58.917
I'm sorry.
You're walking on egg shells?

33:58.917 --> 34:00.659
What do you think
it's been like for me?

34:00.659 --> 34:02.421
I don't know.
I don't know.

34:02.421 --> 34:04.463
I know this whole thing
is weird.

34:04.463 --> 34:07.666
Yeah, it's weird,
and...hard.

34:07.666 --> 34:09.047
Agreed. It's hard.
I don't like it.

34:09.047 --> 34:10.429
-I don't either.
-Well, what do you want to do?

34:10.429 --> 34:12.301
I don't know.
Move out, I guess.

34:15.053 --> 34:17.266
What?

34:17.266 --> 34:19.768
Well,
Arizona says that I can.

34:19.768 --> 34:23.142
I mean, I'm --
I'm healed, so...

34:23.142 --> 34:25.734
I will, like, I guess.

34:25.734 --> 34:28.066
I mean, does that mean, like,
right away, or what do you --

34:28.066 --> 34:30.068
As soon as makes sense.

34:30.068 --> 34:32.241
Right.

34:32.241 --> 34:33.692
Well, uh...

34:36.155 --> 34:37.656
[ Sighs ]

34:37.656 --> 34:39.328
She just slept
right through that.

34:42.701 --> 34:46.795
Yeah, she can be, um...

34:46.795 --> 34:49.628
pretty quiet
when she wants to be.

34:51.710 --> 34:54.052
[ Sighs ]

35:00.139 --> 35:01.980
I don't want you
to move out.

35:03.852 --> 35:05.854
I don't want to
move out, either.

35:09.778 --> 35:11.990
I'm scared
I may never sleep again.

35:11.990 --> 35:14.403
She's stronger than I am.
She could defeat me.

35:14.403 --> 35:16.034
There's two of us.

35:16.034 --> 35:18.287
We got her outnumbered.

35:20.449 --> 35:22.161
You two are staying.

35:25.083 --> 35:26.084
Okay.

35:26.084 --> 35:28.167
Okay.

35:28.167 --> 35:30.169
She's sleeping.
Why the hell aren't we?

35:30.169 --> 35:31.880
I don't know.

35:31.880 --> 35:33.672
I'm just gonna go
set up the coffee thing
for the morning.

35:33.672 --> 35:35.964
Please don't. Okay?
It's enough with the coffee.

35:35.964 --> 35:37.176
-No?
-No.

35:37.176 --> 35:38.637
Okay.

35:48.437 --> 35:49.438
Night.

35:49.438 --> 35:50.729
Night.

35:52.150 --> 35:54.072
[ Crickets chirping ]

36:01.240 --> 36:03.041
You know
you can tell me anything.

36:05.874 --> 36:08.126
I know.

36:08.126 --> 36:09.628
Okay.

36:09.628 --> 36:10.879
Night.

36:22.180 --> 36:27.686
There was this man
I loved very much.

36:29.268 --> 36:31.360
And we loved
taking drugs together,

36:31.360 --> 36:33.862
and one night
we took a lot.

36:36.315 --> 36:39.908
And...the next morning
I woke up,

36:39.908 --> 36:41.910
and he had O.D.'d

36:41.910 --> 36:44.323
and aspirated on his vomit
and...

36:44.323 --> 36:45.744
died.

36:53.211 --> 36:55.133
[ Sniffles ]

36:55.133 --> 36:57.135
I told you it's bad.

37:13.982 --> 37:15.654
I once, um...

37:18.947 --> 37:21.069
I once choked Cristina.

37:24.032 --> 37:27.826
I-I didn't mean to,
but, uh, I was asleep.

37:30.248 --> 37:32.501
I had this ceiling fan.

37:32.501 --> 37:36.044
And in my head,
the blades, it was...

37:36.044 --> 37:38.877
In my head,
it was a helicopter.

37:40.719 --> 37:43.722
And I thought
I was back there.

37:47.936 --> 37:50.058
And I woke up,
and I was choking her.

38:07.746 --> 38:10.168
We're okay, right?

38:15.293 --> 38:17.716
We're okay.

38:19.468 --> 38:22.010
And our kids will be okay?

38:23.802 --> 38:25.684
Our kids will be amazing.

38:32.230 --> 38:35.934
They will.

38:35.934 --> 38:37.696
I can't wait.

38:43.572 --> 38:46.365
So, let's not, then.

38:46.365 --> 38:48.827
Let's not wait.

38:50.909 --> 38:53.211
[ West's "Sleeping at Last"
plays ]

39:13.772 --> 39:18.477
I can't do
what we did today again.

39:23.982 --> 39:26.405
Okay.

39:26.405 --> 39:28.787
I can't have another case

39:28.787 --> 39:33.371
where I question
my medical decisions or yours.

39:33.371 --> 39:35.704
I can't do my job
if I'm thinking about

39:35.704 --> 39:37.916
what you're thinking
about me.

39:40.919 --> 39:43.502
So,
you're thinking about me?

39:43.502 --> 39:45.714
♪ Maps stretched out ♪

39:45.714 --> 39:47.005
I don't want to be.

39:47.005 --> 39:49.598
♪ Too many miles ♪

39:49.598 --> 39:53.562
Let's just be colleagues.

39:53.562 --> 39:55.273
Nothing more.

39:55.273 --> 39:56.605
Colleagues?

39:56.605 --> 39:58.437
Sounds stuffy.

39:58.437 --> 40:01.189
It's not.

40:01.189 --> 40:02.651
It's --

40:02.651 --> 40:05.864
Colleagues are people who hang
out at work and talk about work.

40:05.864 --> 40:07.365
Still sounds stuffy.

40:07.365 --> 40:10.659
Well,
it's what I'm offering.

40:10.659 --> 40:12.791
I don't see why
we can't be friends.

40:12.791 --> 40:14.372
Maggie:
Who can't be friends?

40:14.372 --> 40:17.335
♪ We'll be just fine ♪

40:17.335 --> 40:18.797
Uh, you and me.

40:21.169 --> 40:24.753
I just feel like things
have been a bit strange.

40:24.753 --> 40:26.715
Like I've made you feel
a little uncomfortable.

40:26.715 --> 40:28.386
God, no.
No, you didn't.

40:28.386 --> 40:29.678
You di-- It's fine.

40:29.678 --> 40:32.471
Of course we can be friends.
We are friends.

40:32.471 --> 40:35.103
All of us, right?
We're all friends.

40:35.103 --> 40:37.516
Great, then.

40:37.516 --> 40:41.820
♪ When half of your heart
has yet to come home ♪

40:41.820 --> 40:43.822
-I should get going.
-Bye.

40:43.822 --> 40:47.776
♪ Every minute's adding up ♪

40:47.776 --> 40:50.619
Thank you
for talking to him.

40:50.619 --> 40:52.871
-Yeah.
-It's awful, but it's --

40:52.871 --> 40:56.535
It's good to have it
out on the table.

40:56.535 --> 40:58.837
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

40:58.837 --> 41:01.379
♪ I can't get you
out of my mind ♪

41:01.379 --> 41:04.252
There's a reason these fixes
are called temporary.

41:04.252 --> 41:06.004
They were never meant
to last forever.

41:06.004 --> 41:09.678
♪ I can't get you
out of my mind ♪

41:09.678 --> 41:12.350
♪ I solemnly swear ♪

41:12.350 --> 41:14.683
So, what happens when
you're faced with a fix

41:14.683 --> 41:16.595
that's more permanent?

41:16.595 --> 41:18.476
Hey.

41:18.476 --> 41:20.268
You ready to go?

41:20.268 --> 41:21.560
Uh, give me a minute.

41:21.560 --> 41:22.941
How was your meeting?

41:22.941 --> 41:25.193
How do the lawyers feel
about your case?

41:25.193 --> 41:27.315
Do you fight it?
Do you try to resist?

41:27.315 --> 41:28.486
I'm going to jail.

41:28.486 --> 41:30.318
God, Alex,
don't say that.

41:30.318 --> 41:32.070
Why not?

41:32.070 --> 41:34.913
You're in
an awfully good mood

41:34.913 --> 41:36.494
for a guy who thinks
he's going to the slammer.

41:38.116 --> 41:41.039
I caught a one-in-a-million case
today, Mer.

41:41.039 --> 41:44.122
It wasn't so terrible.

41:44.122 --> 41:47.966
Or do you step back and decide
that maybe acceptance...

41:47.966 --> 41:50.088
I'm good.

41:50.088 --> 41:51.680
Okay, let's go.

41:51.680 --> 41:53.682
...is the best fix of all?

41:53.682 --> 41:56.635
♪ Till our compass
stands still ♪

